  "articleSummary": "This article argues that effective team collaboration is sustained by four interconnected pillars: Psychological Safety, Speed, Clarity, and Commitment. It provides a practical, checklist-style framework for engineering and cross-functional teams to establish clear norms, streamline proposal workflows, and normalize rapid, low-stakes feedback loops. The tone is instructional and analytical, using the \"four pillars\" as a consistent structural metaphor while emphasizing empathy and a \"culture of error\" to encourage idea sharing. The intended audience includes team leads, engineering managers, and product owners seeking to optimize internal decision-making processes and measure collaborative health.",
